bug.short_desc: ibus-typing-booster sometimes shows weird number after candidates when using French
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1239015 ibus-typing-booster-shows-weird-numbers-behind-candidates-in-french.png
When using the French version of ibus-typing-booster, sometimes candidates are shown with weird numbers behind the actual candidate. For example when typing “differem” a candidate
différemment 8
is shown and when selecting it, “différemment8” is actually committed.
See attached screenshot.
